## Frequently Asked Questions

**Can a new company get a building loan?**  
It's harder, but not impossible. If you have strong directors (with good personal income/assets), a clear business model, and contracts/orders to show future revenue, some lenders will consider it. Expect a higher down payment (30-40%) and possibly personal guarantees.

**What if I want to buy and renovate?**  
Some lenders offer "purchase + renovation" packages. The renovation cost (up to 30% of property value) is added to the loan amount and disbursed in stages as work is completed. You'll need contractor quotes and a renovation plan.

**Can I use my existing property as collateral instead of a down payment?**  
Yes, if you already own property (personal or business) with enough equity, you can use it as collateral to reduce the cash down payment. This is called cross-collateralization.

**How long does approval take?**  
Initial approval: 5-7 days (assuming complete documents).  
Full approval and disbursement: 4-8 weeks (includes property valuation, legal work, and loan documentation).

**Do I need a guarantor?**  
For most SME building loans, the company directors act as guarantors. If the company is very new or has limited assets, additional personal guarantees (from other directors or shareholders) may be required.

**Can I refinance an existing building loan?**  
Absolutely. If you've been paying for a few years and your business has grown, refinancing can get you a lower interest rate or release equity for other business needs.

